 learning and technical mastery.Drive pre-sales activities by leading technical responses to bids, conducting technical due diligence, and shaping new opportunities with potential clients.Represent Hippo Digital in the wider tech community through public speaking, blogging, and contributing to open-source or community initiatives.Act as the final point of escalation for complex technical decisions, ensuring our solutions are secure, sustainable, and scalable.About the Candidate:Essential ExperienceExtensive experience in software development with a deep, expert-level command of at least two of the following: Python, Node or Java.A proven track record of leading large-scale, enterprise-level engineering projects and digital transformations.Demonstrated experience building and deploying applications on major public cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP), with a deep understanding of cloud-native patterns.Hands-on experience with containerisation (Docker, Kubernetes) and designing advanced CI/CD pipelines (e.g., GitLab CI/CD, GitHub Actions).Strong proficiency in Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC), specifically using Terraform for complex, repeatable deployments.Proven ability to communicate complex technical concepts effectively to C-suite and executive-level stakeholders.Experience in a consultancy environment, including contributing to pre-sales, proposals, and project scoping.Expert-level knowledge of application security, distributed systems, and performance tuning in a cloud context. Experience building, scaling, and managing high-performing engineering teams, with a focus on fostering an inclusive culture and driving delivery excellence.Highly Desirable Experience: Proven expertise in implementing robust identity solutions, including deep knowledge of OAuth2, OIDC, SAML, and integrating modern CIAM providers (e.g. Auth0, ForgeRock, or Azure AD).About The CompanyAs well as a competitive salary which we’re transparent about from the outset, you can also expect a range of 